cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on capturing semantic relations of words in a vector space. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel model that uses neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with data sparseness, which is a common problem in information retrieval, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses embeddings, which is a common technique in neural networks, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
